scholars reflects different writing traditions.

23
00:01:23,860 --> 00:01:27,140
We’re going to focus on the second one,
found in Genesis 2.

24
00:01:27,140 --> 00:01:33,220
As we join our story, God has already created
the the earth and the heavens and man to till

25
00:01:33,220 --> 00:01:37,030
the earth, because as we established last
time: Gods don’t like weeding.

26
00:01:37,030 --> 00:01:41,869
Unlike the first version of creation in Genesis,
man is created near the very beginning, which

27
00:01:41,869 --> 00:01:45,920
suggests that he’s actually pretty important
in the grand scheme of things.

28
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:50,479
But apparently one man wasn’t enough for
all that Edenic gardening.

29
00:01:50,479 --> 00:01:55,490
Genesis 2 verse 21 begins:
So the Lord God caused a deep sleep to fall

30
